# Python Runtime And Operations

- Handle exceptions explicitly and never swallow errors silently.
- Log failures with actionable context for debugging.
- Use environment variables for configuration; never hardcode secrets.
- Validate required configuration early at startup.
- Manage dependencies with a lockfile (uv/poetry/pip-tools) and keep them minimal.
